cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use this software, its data, or its results, please cite it as below."
title: >-
  Inserted Layers + SFT Match LoRA + RL on GSM8K at 60x Less Compute,
  and Can Be Trained Without Re-using Gold Answers via Distillation
abstract: >-
  Code, evaluation outputs, and figure-regeneration scripts accompanying a
  controlled comparison of low-rank adaptation (LoRA) against inserting new
  full-rank transformer layers into a frozen base for GSM8K math reasoning,
  on Llama-3.1 8B and Llama-3.2 3B. SFT into two inserted layers matches
  LoRA + GRPO within seed noise at roughly 60x lower training compute; a
  distillation procedure re-encodes a trained LoRA into inserted layers
  without re-using gold answers.
